de.wwu.muggl.instructions.interfaces.control
Interface JumpInvocation

All Known Implementing Classes:
Invoke, Invokeinterface, Invokespecial, Invokestatic, InvokestaticQuickAbstract, InvokestaticQuickNative, InvokestaticQuickNormal, InvokestaticReplacer, Invokevirtual
public interface JumpInvocation

Interface that is to be implemented by any instruction that will invoke another method. If this interface is implemented, the interfaces JumpAlways, JumpConditional, JumpNever and JumpSwicthing must not be implemented. (JumpException may be implemented.)

Version:
1.0.0, 2010-03-10
Author:
Tim Majchrzak
